README OF CAPI2NAME - AN ISDN CAPI MONITOR WITH WEB INTERFACE
--------------------------------------------------------------

quick install:
-------------
1.) create a database and user in the mysql (see below)
2.) type make and make install
3.) Now capi2name HTDOCS-File are installed in /usr/share/capi2name
4.) You can configure your apache Webserver (see below)
3.) open your web browser and open http://localhost/c2n/up_inst/
4.) Gotto the install selection
5.) write down your database and user information and press the button
6.) open with vim or another editor the /usr/sharecapi2name/includes/conf.inc.php
7.) write down your database and user information and save the file.
8.) Delete the up_inst/ folder
9.) open your webbrowser and open http://localhost/c2n/admin/
10.) Login with the admin password 'admin' and create a now user and change the admin password
12.) open with vi or another editor /etc/capi2name.conf 
13.) write down your database and user inforation
14.) start the daemon programm with /usr/sbin/capi2name (logfile is /var/log/daemon.log)
15.) call yourself and test if you can see your call in the webbrowser



Apache Configuration:
---------------------------------
Alias /c2n    "/usr/share/capi2name"
<Directory /usr/share/capi2name>
     AllowOverride None
     Options -ExecCGI -Indexes -MultiViews -SymLinksIfOwnerMatch -FollowSymlinks</Directory>

---------------------------------



Create a Mysql database and user for capi2name:
----------------------------------------------
1.) go to the mysql console: mysql -u root -p
2.) now you are on the Mysql root console
3.) type `create database capidb;` (this command without the ` creates a new database named 'capidb')
4.) create a mysql user:
    `GRANT SELECT,INSERT,UPDATE,DELETE,DROP,ALTER.CREATE ON capidb.* TO 'capi'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'passwd';
    This command creates a user 'capi' that can access from localhost the database 'capidb' with the password 'passwd'
5.) mysql musst reload the user tables: `flush privileges;



->On the Webpage you can find an better install manual and FAQ selection.


When you have problems go to the user help forum, you can find it on the webpage.


